{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852205805,"sessionID":"ses_286f8510dffe7Btj6SgyzgA8f7","part":{"id":"prt_d79096fba0012xOVl297WqjeJG","messageID":"msg_d790965b0001FasU77fMXj9jGt","sessionID":"ses_286f8510dffe7Btj6SgyzgA8f7","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_563c54e58e7944b7b3003a96","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-021: CLI build 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `build` command entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `build` subcommand on the Typer application that orchestrates container image creation from a previously packaged workspace.\n\n#### Scenario: Command signature and options\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and the user runs `agentcube build --help`\n- **WHEN** the help text is displayed\n- **THEN** it SHALL show the following options:\n  - `-f, --workspace TEXT` — Path to the agent workspace directory (default: `.`)\n  - `-p, --proxy TEXT` — Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n  - `--cloud-provider TEXT` — Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n  - `--output TEXT` — Output path for build artifacts\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: Default option values\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube build` with no options\n- **WHEN** the command resolves its arguments\n- **THEN** the values SHALL be:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"`\n  - `proxy` = `None`\n  - `cloud_provider` = `None`\n  - `output` = `None`\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path resolution\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a workspace path via `-f` or `--workspace`\n- **WHEN** the command starts execution\n- **THEN** the path SHALL be resolved to an absolute `Path` object before being passed to `BuildRuntime`\n\n### Requirement: Build mode resolution\n\nThe system SHALL determine the build strategy (local vs cloud) from workspace metadata, with CLI overrides taking precedence.\n\n#### Scenario: Default to local build mode\n- **GIVEN** a workspace with `agent_metadata.yaml` containing `build_mode: local` (or no `build_mode` field)\n- **WHEN** the `build` command runs without `--cloud-provider`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute a local Docker build via `BuildRuntime._build_local`\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build mode via cloud provider flag\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--cloud-provider huawei`\n- **WHEN** the command resolves the build mode\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute a cloud build via `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` regardless of metadata `build_mode`\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build mode from metadata\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `build_mode: cloud`\n- **WHEN** the `build` command runs without `--cloud-provider`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute a cloud build via `BuildRuntime._build_cloud`\n\n### Requirement: Build prerequisites validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate all prerequisites before attempting a build.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker availability check for local builds\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `DockerService.check_docker_available()` and raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if Docker is unavailable\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace packaging validation\n- **GIVEN** the workspace has not been packaged (no `agent_metadata.yaml` exists)\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the workspace must be packaged first\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata load success\n- **GIVEN** a valid `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` loads metadata\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `MetadataService.load_metadata` to parse the file into an `AgentMetadata` object\n\n### Requirement: Version increment on build\n\nThe system SHALL automatically increment the semantic version in metadata before building and handle rollback on failure.\n\n#### Scenario: Patch version increment\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.2.3\"` (valid semver `X.Y.Z`)\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version` runs\n- **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"1.2.4\"` (patch bumped)\n\n#### Scenario: Append `.1` for non-semver versions\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.0-beta\"` (not valid semver)\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version` runs\n- **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"1.0-beta.1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Fallback version when version is None\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version` runs\n- **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"0.0.1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Version rollback on build failure\n- **GIVEN** the version was incremented before the build\n- **WHEN** `_build_local` or `_build_cloud` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the system SHALL revert `metadata.version` to its original value before re-raising\n\n### Requirement: Local Docker build\n\nThe system SHALL build a container image using the local Docker daemon when `build_mode` is `local`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful local build\n- **GIVEN** Docker is available and the workspace contains a valid `Dockerfile` (generated by `pack`)\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_local` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Resolve the image name from metadata (or derive from `agent_name`)\n  2. Call `DockerService.build_image` with the workspace `Dockerfile` path\n  3. Pass `build_args` containing proxy settings if `--proxy` was provided\n  4. Tag the image with the incremented version (default `\"latest\"` if no version)\n  5. Return a dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy configuration for local build\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** `build_args` SHALL include `{\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Build with custom output path\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--output /tmp/build-artifacts`\n- **WHEN** the local build completes\n- **THEN** build artifacts (if any) SHALL be saved or referenced at the specified output path\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build failure\n- **GIVEN** the `Dockerfile` has syntax errors or build steps fail\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise a `docker.errors.BuildError` which propagates through `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario: Image tag from metadata version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.2.4\"` after increment\n- **WHEN** `_build_local` tags the image\n- **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `{image_name}:1.2.4`\n\n### Requirement: Cloud build\n\nThe system SHALL trigger a remote build on the specified cloud provider when `build_mode` is `cloud`.\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build with provider\n- **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider huawei` is passed\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Authenticate with the cloud provider (using configured credentials)\n  2. Upload the workspace contents to the cloud build service\n  3. Trigger the build with the specified proxy (if any)\n  4. Poll for build completion\n  5. Return a dict with cloud build result metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build without provider configured\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` but no `--cloud-provider` is passed and metadata lacks provider config\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the cloud provider must be specified\n\n### Requirement: Build metadata update\n\nThe system SHALL update workspace metadata with build results upon successful completion.\n\n#### Scenario: Update build metadata on success\n- **GIVEN** a successful local or cloud build\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Update `metadata.image` with the built image information (`image_name`, `image_id`, `tag`)\n  2. Persist the updated metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` via `MetadataService.save_metadata`\n  3. Include `build_time` in the metadata if available\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata update with custom tag\n- **GIVEN** the build succeeded and a specific tag is provided\n- **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata` runs with `tag=\"v1.2.4\"`\n- **THEN** the metadata `image` field SHALL include `\"tag\": \"v1.2.4\"`\n\n### Requirement: CLI success output\n\nThe system SHALL display a Rich-formatted success message after a successful build.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful build output\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` completes without exception\n- **WHEN** the `build` command finishes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print:\n  - A success message with the agent name\n  - The resolved workspace path\n  - The built image name and tag\n  - Build duration (if available)\n  - Using Rich markup for formatting\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose build output\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is passed\n- **WHEN** the build runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display detailed logging including:\n  - Build mode resolution\n  - Prerequisites validation steps\n  - Docker build stream output (for local builds)\n  - Metadata update confirmation\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle build failures gracefully with appropriate error messages.\n\n#### Scenario: Build error with verbose flag\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` is `True`\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  1. Print `Error building agent: {e}` in red\n  2. Print a full traceback\n  3. Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Build error without verbose flag\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` is `False`\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  1. Print `Error building agent: {e}` in red\n  2. Exit with code `1` (no traceback)\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is invalid\n\n### Requirement: Progress indication\n\nThe system SHALL display a Rich `Progress` spinner during the build operation.\n\n#### Scenario: Progress spinner during build\n- **GIVEN** the build command is running\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` is executing\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL show a Rich `Progress` spinner with the text `\"Building agent...\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Progress completion\n- **GIVEN** the build completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the spinner stops\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL replace the spinner with a success checkmark and summary\n\n## File changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Modify | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `build` Typer command with options and error handling |\n| Modify | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Implement `build`, `_increment_version`, `_validate_build_prerequisites`, `_build_local`, `_build_cloud`, `_update_build_metadata` |\n| Modify | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Implement `build_image` with proxy build_args support |\n| Modify | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Ensure `load_metadata` and `save_metadata` support build workflow |\n| Modify | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Ensure `BuildRuntime` is exported |\n| Add | `tests/cli/test_build.py` | CLI build command tests |\n| Add | `tests/runtime/test_build_runtime.py` | BuildRuntime unit tests |\n| Add | `tests/services/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService build tests |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775852205788,"end":1775852205803}}}}
